==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indefeasible
<hw>In`de*fea`si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>defeasible</ets>: cf. OF.
<ets>indefaisable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not to be defeated; not defeasible;
incapable of being annulled or made void; <as>as, an
<ex>indefeasible</ex> or title</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That the king had a divine and an <qex>indefeasible</qex> right to
the regal power.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indefectibility</ent>⟦br⟧
